 # Codex Writer Findings — PublicMenu
-Chain: publicmenu-260321-195108
+Chain: publicmenu-260321-200456
 
 ## Findings
-1. [P1] Hall submit validates before the Bottom Sheet gate — In `pages/PublicMenu/base/x.jsx`, `handleSubmitOrder()` calls `validate()` before the just-in-time table-confirmation check. `validate()` rejects hall submits when `!currentTableId`, but that error is stored as `errors.tableSelection` and is not rendered anywhere in the current drawer flow. Result: on `/x?partner=...&mode=hall` a new guest can tap "Отправить официанту" and get a silent no-op instead of the confirmation sheet. FIX: move the `orderMode === "hall" && !isTableVerified` interception before `validate()`, or skip `tableSelection` validation until after the sheet verifies the table.
-2. [P1] Pickup/delivery checkout still drops loyalty and discount UI — `pages/PublicMenu/base/x.jsx` passes `showLoyaltySection`, `customerEmail`, `loyaltyAccount`, `earnedPoints`, `redeemedPoints`, `maxRedeemPoints`, `discountAmount`, and related props into `CheckoutView`, but `pages/PublicMenu/base/CheckoutView.jsx` neither accepts nor renders them. Users in pickup/delivery lose the email, points, redeem, and discount flows on the actual checkout screen. FIX: add the missing props to `CheckoutView` and render the loyalty block there, or extract the existing loyalty UI into a shared checkout section.
-3. [P2] Table-confirmation state lives in hidden `CartView` instead of the visible Bottom Sheet — After inline verification UI was removed, `pages/PublicMenu/base/CartView.jsx` still owns `codeAttempts`, `codeLockedUntil`, `codeSecondsLeft`, and the auto-verify effect bound to `tableCodeInput`, while the visible input now lives in the Bottom Sheet in `pages/PublicMenu/base/x.jsx`. That means the sheet shows only `codeVerificationError` with no attempt/cooldown feedback, and verification can be triggered by an off-screen component before the CTA tap. FIX: move attempt/lockout/auto-verify state into `x.jsx` with the Bottom Sheet, or remove the hidden auto-verify effect and let the sheet CTA own verification.
-4. [P2] Mobile grid partner setting is ignored — `pages/PublicMenu/base/MenuView.jsx` computes `mobileCols` from `partner.menu_grid_mobile`, but the actual grid render hardcodes `isMobile ? 'grid-cols-2' : gridColsClass`. Any partner configured for a 1-column mobile menu still gets 2 columns. FIX: use the computed mobile class (`MOBILE_GRID[mobileCols]`) in the mobile branch instead of the hardcoded `grid-cols-2`.
-5. [P2] `useTableSession` loses restored guests that only have `_id` — The hook correctly defines `normalizeGuestId()`, but later syncs `currentGuestIdRef.current = currentGuest?.id || null` in `pages/PublicMenu/base/useTableSession.jsx`. If a restored `SessionGuest` only carries `_id`, the ref is reset to `null`, so polling keeps re-running guest restore and downstream logic can behave as if no current guest exists. FIX: store `normalizeGuestId(currentGuest)` in the ref, and align any other guest-id reads in this file with the same normalization rule.
-6. [P3] Several control labels still regress i18n/accessibility — `pages/PublicMenu/base/CheckoutView.jsx` hardcodes `aria-label="Decrease"` / `aria-label="Increase"`, `pages/PublicMenu/base/CartView.jsx` hardcodes the reward-email placeholder `email@example.com`, and `pages/PublicMenu/base/MenuView.jsx` list-mode add/remove buttons plus `CartView` icon-only controls are missing localized accessible labels. This leaves mixed-language assistive text and unlabeled mobile controls in production. FIX: replace hardcoded assistive/user-facing strings with `t()/tr()` and add `aria-label` to icon-only/list-stepper buttons.
+1. [P1] Partner lookup swallows backend failures as "not found" — In `x.jsx:1322-1345`, both partner lookup attempts catch and suppress request errors, then `x.jsx:3035-3040` renders `error.partner_not_found` for any `null` result. A transient Base44/network failure is misreported as a bad QR link, which blocks retryable recovery. FIX: keep query errors separate from real "no partner found", and render a retryable error state for failed requests instead of collapsing everything to `null`.
+2. [P1] Hall StickyCartBar ignores visit lifecycle state — In `x.jsx:2101-2144`, the sticky bar mode is derived only from `cart`, `myOrders`, and `sessionOrders`, with four states total. Context in `README.md`/`BUGS.md` shows the production flow needs visit-state-driven behavior (paid, closed, reset, bill-requested, text-mode variants). The current logic can show the wrong CTA/amount/visibility for real hall sessions. FIX: derive sticky-bar state from table-session lifecycle data, then map CTA text, subtitle, visibility, and totals from that explicit state machine.
+3. [P2] Translation fallback chain does not match the documented behavior — The comment at `x.jsx:321-324` says the chain is "selected lang -> EN fallback -> RU fallback -> empty string", but `makeSafeT()` at `x.jsx:523-541` only calls the current translator and then jumps straight to the hardcoded fallback map; `tr()` at `x.jsx:1229-1231` also falls back to inline Russian strings. Missing translations can therefore leak Russian copy to non-RU guests instead of an English fallback. FIX: implement the documented locale chain explicitly, or provide locale-aware fallback dictionaries and remove page-level Russian literals as universal fallbacks.
+4. [P2] Number and time formatting ignore the selected in-app language — `OrderStatusScreen.formatPrice()` uses `num.toLocaleString()` at `x.jsx:982-989`, and `formatOrderTime()` uses `toLocaleTimeString(undefined, ...)` at `x.jsx:1216-1221`. The page supports runtime language switching via `useI18n()`, but these formatters stay tied to the browser default locale. FIX: derive a locale from `lang` and pass it through to all number/time formatters, including `OrderStatusScreen`.
+5. [P2] Table-code confirmation sheet regresses on narrow phones for long codes — The bottom sheet renders fixed-width code boxes (`w-10`, `gap-2`) and a fixed-width input (`w-40`) at `x.jsx:3416-3442`. For 6-8 digit table codes this layout can overflow or compress badly on small devices, which is a mobile-first regression. FIX: make the code UI responsive (`w-8 sm:w-10`, tighter gaps, optional wrapping/scaling) and size the hidden input to the configured `tableCodeLength`.
